<exercise>
  <title>C4 - Homogeneous second-order linear IVP (ver. 44)</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Find the solution to the given IVP.</p>
    <me>y''+4y'+3y = 0 \hspace{1em} y(0) = -2 , y'(0) = 12</me>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>y= 3 \, e^{\left(-t\right)} - 5 \, e^{\left(-3 \, t\right)}</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
